purpose?\n<Serena>

though it's still a very vague story.\n<Cecilia>

touch with the world as you just waltzed right in
front of me.\n<Cecilia>

It clicked. I thought there must be something to
it and hit the jackpot.\n<Cecilia>

And once your secret was out, you couldn't really
refuse the job. Who knows what could happen.\n<Cecilia>

It would have been troublesome for me if you had
run away. Though I didn't expect such trouble.\n<Cecilia>
Do I still need to make more of an appeal?\n<Cecilia>

Don't you have a job you want to ask of me? Of
this capable information broker, Cecilia-san here.\n<Cecilia>

Indeed. I would like to request your services. You
are precisely the person I've been seeking.\n<Serena>

Information broker Cecilia. Valadon-sama. Please
find my unicorn... Splendor.\n<Serena>
Yes, yes, that's more like it.\n<Cecilia>

ストーリー　シシリア調査報告
There's no turning back now. Are you ready?\n<Cecilia>

First, I need Serena to go to the guild and accept
a certain request.\n<Cecilia>

mouth right now, not having a clue.\n<Cecilia>

It's a dark deal, so normally only those involved
with the guild's underbelly would be assigned to
it.\n<Cecilia>

failure. That's very convenient for us right now.\n<Cecilia>

Right. If we can successfully accept the request,
we'll create chaos at the scene and crush the
deal.\n<Cecilia>

Then the job fails. Serena will be expected to pay
millions of G in damages to the guild.\n<Cecilia>

will be in trouble. After all, a mere adventurer
couldn't possibly come up with that kind of money.\n<Cecilia>

That's where I come in again, pretending to be
Ganuron... I'll suggest auctioning off Serena.\n<Cecilia>

I'll argue in Ganuron's name how valuable Serena
is and how much money she can bring in. I could
even guarantee to pay any shortfall on Ganuron's
behalf.\n<Cecilia>

Since Ganuron nominated Serena, it becomes his
responsibility too, so this intervention will seem
natural. It's a clever part of my strategy.
Killing two birds with one stone through a self-
staged play?\n<Cecilia>

And what's more, that guy usually doesn't show his
face. Instead, who's been his messenger? None
other than moi.\n<Cecilia>
It's amazing how well all the pieces fit together.\n<Serena>
It pays to do someone's errands.\n<Cecilia>

know what kind of language Ganuron would use. It's
impossible to keep it up forever, but I'm
confident I can pull it off this one time.\n<Cecilia>
